OL,3,CPolice complaints not properly
OL,4,Cinvestigated, politician alleges
OL,6,FHe alleged that a man was "punched,
OL,7,Fchoked unconscious, then arrested for
OL,8,Fa crime he did not commit" and was
OL,9,F"refused help" by the Guernsey Police
OL,10,FComplaints Commission when the man
OL,11,Ftried to raise the issue of being
OL,12,Fmistreated by police officers.
OL,14,FDeputy Curgenven adds that the man's
OL,15,F"mental and physical health took a
OL,16,Fturn for the worse" and his family's
OL,17,Fcompany no longer work with the police.
OL,19,FHe argues that a loss of trust could
OL,20,Fhave been prevented by "a functioning,
OL,21,Findependent watchdog".
