OL,3,CPolice complaints not properly
OL,4,Cinvestigated, politician alleges
OL,6,FEven when they monitor complaints,
OL,7,FDeputy Curgenven says the Commission
OL,8,F"has been criticised for acting as a
OL,9,Frubber stamp", given that "in the 14
OL,10,Fyears it has been up and running, the
OL,11,FCommission has never upheld an appeal
OL,12,Fon the basis it disagrees with the
OL,13,Fpolice".
OL,15,FHe adds: "Even had the Commission
OL,16,Fwanted to help complainants, it would
OL,17,Fhave been unable to. For its powers
OL,18,Fare limited to observation only; it
OL,19,Fcannot change the outcome of a police
OL,20,Fdecision."
