OL,3,CPolice complaints not properly
OL,4,Cinvestigated, politician alleges
OL,6,FThe Commission's report states that
OL,7,Fcomplaints are "primarily processed"
OL,8,Fby an independent department within
OL,9,FGuernsey Police.
OL,11,FFor concerns over officers below the
OL,12,Frank of Superintendent, the Chief of
OL,13,FPolice is designated the "appropriate
OL,14,Fauthority" in law, while this
OL,15,Fresponsibility falls to the Home
OL,16,FAffairs Committee for more senior
OL,17,Fofficers.
