OL,3,CPolice complaints not properly
OL,4,Cinvestigated, politician alleges
OL,6,FDeputy Curgenven says the speech "is
OL,7,Fnot an attack on individuals" and a
OL,8,Fmore robust complaints process will
OL,9,Fprotect officers too, "By
OL,10,Fdistinguishing honest error from
OL,11,Fmisconduct; by fixing what is fixable;
OL,12,Fand by proving where the police got it
OL,13,Fright".
OL,15,FDeputy Curgenven concludes that "the
OL,16,Fpace of reform has been unacceptably
OL,17,Fslow. And that the reforms put in
OL,18,Fmotion by the prior Committee are
OL,19,Fsimply not good enough".
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/8
